OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1784058473
OL,3,CPolice chief defends investigation
OL,4,Cinto Ann Widdecombe's death
OL,6,F"There's been some commentary about
OL,7,Fthe way Devon and Cornwall police have
OL,8,Fcommunicated during the early stages
OL,9,Fof this case but, as the Home
OL,10,FSecretary said yesterday, it is not
OL,11,Funusual that in a fast-paced
OL,12,Finvestigation, more information comes
OL,13,Fto light that changes the nature or
OL,14,Fthe character of what the police are
OL,15,Fdealing with," she said.
OL,26,@nD@AOUwD@NO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/8
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1784058473
OL,3,CPolice chief defends investigation
OL,4,Cinto Ann Widdecombe's death
OL,6,F"Since the beginning of this
OL,7,Finvestigation, I have been briefed by
OL,8,Fthe chief constable regularly, and I
OL,9,Fam confident that Devon and Cornwall
OL,10,FPolice has provided a substantial and
OL,11,Fprofessional response to Ann
OL,12,FWiddecombe's death.
OL,14,F"I am particularly grateful to members
OL,15,Fof the public, who have provided
OL,16,Finformation and assisted officers in
OL,17,Fprogressing the investigation.
OL,26,@vD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/8
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,404,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1784058473
OL,3,CPolice chief defends investigation
OL,4,Cinto Ann Widdecombe's death
OL,6,F"My thoughts remain with Ann's family
OL,7,Fand friends. I have been touched by
OL,8,Fthe stories I have heard from those
OL,9,Fwho lived closed to her on Dartmoor.
OL,11,F"Whatever you thought of her politics,
OL,12,FAnn was an exceptionally likeable
OL,13,Fcharacter.
OL,15,F"When I visited the scene on Sunday, I
OL,16,Fwas impressed by the efforts being
OL,17,Fmade by the police to speak to
OL,18,Fresidents and address their very
OL,19,Funderstandable concerns."
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUwD@AOU{D@YO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/8
